b">·</span></span></div><span>Mar 18</span></div></span></div></span></div></div></div><div class="ab co hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih ii ij ik il im in io"><div class="h k w je jf q"><div class="jg l"><div class="ab q jh"><div class="pw-multi-vote-icon go ho ji jj jk"><div class=""><div class="jl jm jn jo jp jq jr am js jt ju jk"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-label="clap"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M11.37.83L12 3.28l.63-2.45h-1.26zM15.42 1.84l-1.18-.39-.34 2.5 1.52-2.1zM9.76 1.45l-1.19.4 1.53 2.1-.34-2.5zM20.25 11.84l-2.5-4.4a1.42 1.42 0 0 0-.93-.64.96.96 0 0 0-.75.18c-.25.19-.4.42-.45.7l.05.05 2.35 4.13c1.62 2.95 1.1 5.78-1.52 8.4l-.46.41c1-.13 1.93-.6 2.78-1.45 2.7-2.7 2.51-5.59 1.43-7.38zM12.07 9.01c-.13-.69.08-1.3.57-1.77l-2.06-2.07a1.12 1.12 0 0 0-1.56 0c-.15.15-.22.34-.27.53L12.07 9z"></path><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M14.74 8.3a1.13 1.13 0 0 0-.73-.5.67.67 0 0 0-.53.13c-.15.12-.59.46-.2 1.3l1.18 2.5a.45.45 0 0 1-.23.76.44.44 0 0 1-.48-.25L7.6 6.11a.82.82 0 1 0-1.15 1.15l3.64 3.64a.45.45 0 1 1-.63.63L5.83 7.9 4.8 6.86a.82.82 0 0 0-1.33.9c.04.1.1.18.18.26l1.02 1.03 3.65 3.64a.44.44 0 0 1-.15.73.44.44 0 0 1-.48-.1L4.05 9.68a.82.82 0 0 0-1.4.57.81.81 0 0 0 .24.58l1.53 1.54 2.3 2.28a.45.45 0 0 1-.64.63L3.8 13a.81.81 0 0 0-1.39.57c0 .22.09.43.24.58l4.4 4.4c2.8 2.8 5.5 4.12 8.68.94 2.27-2.28 2.71-4.6 1.34-7.1l-2.32-4.08z"></path></svg></div></div></div><div class="pw-multi-vote-count l jv jw jx jy jz ka kb"><p class="be b kc z hb"><span class="jm">--</span></p></div></div></div><div><div class="bl" aria-hidden="false"><button class="ao jl ke kf ab q jn kg kh" aria-label="responses"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-label="responses" class="kd"><path d="M18 16.8a7.14 7.14 0 0 0 2.24-5.32c0-4.12-3.53-7.48-8.05-7.48C7.67 4 4 7.36 4 11.48c0 4.13 3.67 7.48 8.2 7.48a8.9 8.9 0 0 0 2.38-.32c.23.2.48.39.75.56 1.06.69 2.2 1.04 3.4 1.04.22 0 .4-.11.48-.29a.5.5 0 0 0-.04-.52 6.4 6.4 0 0 1-1.16-2.65v.02zm-3.12 1.06l-.06-.22-.32.1a8 8 0 0 1-2.3.33c-4.03 0-7.3-2.96-7.3-6.59S8.17 4.9 12.2 4.9c4 0 7.1 2.96 7.1 6.6 0 1.8-.6 3.47-2.02 4.72l-.2.16v.26l.02.3a6.74 6.74 0 0 0 .88 2.4 5.27 5.27 0 0 1-2.17-.86c-.28-.17-.72-.38-.94-.59l.01-.02z"></path></svg><p class="be b kc z hb"><span class="pw-responses-count ki kd">3</span></p></button></div></div></div><div class="ab q ip iq ir is it iu iv iw ix iy iz ja jb jc jd"><div class="kj k j i d"></div><div class="h k"></div><div class="ec sc cm"><div class="l ae"><div class="ab ca"><div class="sd se sf sg sh lp ch bg"><div class="ab"><div class="bl bg" aria-hidden="false"><div><div class="bl" aria-hidden="false"><button class="af jn ah ai aj ak al kk an ao ap he kl km kh kn ko kp kq kr s ks kt ku kv kw kx ky u kz la lb"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 1 18 0 9 9 0 0 1-18 0zm9-10a10 10 0 1 0 0 20 10 10 0 0 0 0-20zm3.38 10.42l-4.6 3.06a.5.5 0 0 1-.78-.41V8.93c0-.4.45-.63.78-.41l4.6 3.06c.3.2.3.64 0 .84z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg><div class="j i d"><p class="be b bf z hb">Listen</p></div></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="bl" aria-hidden="false" aria-describedby="postFooterSocialMenu" aria-labelledby="postFooterSocialMenu"><div><div class="bl" aria-hidden="false"><button class="af jn ah ai aj ak al kk an ao ap he kl km kh kn ko kp kq kr s ks kt ku kv kw kx ky u kz la lb"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M15.22 4.93a.42.42 0 0 1-.12.13h.01a.45.45 0 0 1-.29.08.52.52 0 0 1-.3-.13L12.5 3v7.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5V3.02l-2 2a.45.45 0 0 1-.57.04h-.02a.4.4 0 0 1-.16-.3.4.4 0 0 1 .1-.32l2.8-2.8a.5.5 0 0 1 .7 0l2.8 2.8a.42.42 0 0 1 .07.5zm-.1.14zm.88 2h1.5a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v10a2 2 0 0 1-2 2h-11a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-10a2 2 0 0 1 2-2H8a.5.5 0 0 1 .35.14c.1.1.15.22.15.35a.5.5 0 0 1-.15.35.5.5 0 0 1-.35.15H6.4c-.5 0-.9.4-.9.9v10.2a.9.9 0 0 0 .9.9h11.2c.5 0 .9-.4.9-.9V8.96c0-.5-.4-.9-.9-.9H16a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg><div class="j i d"><p class="be b bf z hb">Share</p></div></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><figure class="lf lg lh li lj lk lc ld paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="ll lm go ln bg lo"><div class="lc ld le"><picture><source srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*cLKG9oELRYyglbBmd3VjAw.jpeg 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bg lp lq c" width="700" height="385" loading="eager" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="lr ls lt lc ld lu lv be b bf z hb">Say hello to J33ves</figcaption></figure><p id="b6e3" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">How many times have you missed a resupply window for your ships in SCORE? This author has missed many. Not for lack of trying but my IRL duties often conflict with my virtual life duties causing many a SCORE crew member to go hungry or to drift in space with no fuel (sorry fellas). Furthermore, when the ships ain’t grinding, they ain’t earning. This is just an irritating fact of the SCORE gameplay loop.</p><p id="fba0" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">When <a class="af mu" href="https://twitter.com/Loid_Official" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Loid</a> from The Club brought my attention to their resupply bot, aka J33ves, I was naturally curious but skeptical. Resource supply is not a new concept. Guilds like HEIM and even The Club’s first iteration (Pitstop) have R4 supply functionality but it’s not automatic, rather “1-click”. [Note: HEIM’s tool is a fork of The Club’s PitStop.] Furthermore, these tools require one to connect a wallet. This was a non-starter for me given all the recent hacks and wallet drains (of which I was a victim). According to Loid, J33ves works differently. You only need to send Atlas to the J33ves wallet and he will handle the rest. No need to connect your wallet.</p><p id="fa7b" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">With the wallet issue removed, I decided to give J33ves a test drive. Initially the sign-up process required verification but The Club has now removed that step. According to Loid:</p><blockquote class="mv mw mx"><p id="ca03" class="lw lx my ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mz mi mj mk na mm mn mo nb mq mr ms mt eo bj">The biggest update to the resupply service is that it’s open to everyone without the need to link your Discord name to a wallet. So completely anonymous and secure. Send ATLAS from the wallet that needs service and J33VES will see which wallet the Atlas came from and create a balance for that address within a few minutes. This can be checked by searching your address on explorer and clicking the J33ves tab. He will start resupplying when there are less than 30 minutes until supplies are empty, using our ‘optimal’ approach. So fully filling the resource with shortest delaying time and ensuring all other resources have that same amount of time remaining also. The caveat with complete anonymity is that there are no refunds!!! So only send what you need. If you want a refund we will have to process this manually which of course means you would have to reveal yourself. There is 0 risk to your ships with this service as there is 0 wallet connectivity. The Atlas you send is the only potential risk and we will endeavour to refund that if something did happen to it.</p></blockquote><p id="1308" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">Getting started</strong></p><p id="f318" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">The easiest way to get started is to go to <a class="af mu" href="http://explorer.staratlas.club" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">explorer.staratlas.club</a> and click on the J33ves tab on the right. Read and accept the Terms of Service by checking the box and then send ATLAS to the wallet address listed. Be sure to also to scroll down and read the FAQ.</p><p id="fa5d" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Once your Atlas is in J33ves, you can sit back and enjoy. <strong class="ly ew">Note:</strong> I transferred 500 Atlas to start but you may need to transfer more or less depending on the size of your fleet.</p><p id="7415" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">Important: </strong>As of March 13, 2023 there is a 20% fee for using the resupply service. Also, the fee can be raised (or lowered) at anytime.</p><figure class="nd ne nf ng nh lk lc ld paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="ll lm go ln bg lo"><div class="lc ld nc"><picture><source srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*beXaNdGaO8Di9X4Y 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bg lp lq c" width="700" height="74" loading="lazy" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div></figure><p id="7c4c" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">However, you are only charged if he has to resupply your fleet. You can beat J33ves to the punch and avoid the fees but what’s the fun in that!</p><p id="8f25" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">To verify or not to verify, that is the question!</strong></p><p id="1ad3" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Many will opt to remain anonymous but there are some downsides to this approach. For one, you don’t get access to all the cool J33ves commands that grant you further insight into your SCORE fleet. You don’t have to become a Club member to use these commands, but you do need to verify your wallet which would require you to reveal your Discord username. Personally, I verified my wallet because I wanted the added functionality.</p><p id="81ab" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Below is the step by step process for getting verified. You can skip this section if you prefer to remain completely anonymous.</p><p id="4e4a" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">Step 1: </strong>You will need to join The Club’s <a class="af mu" href="http://discord.gg/the-sa-club" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Discord</a>.</p><p id="6d27" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">Step 2:</strong> Head over to “the read this for access” channel, react to become a member (this is to stop bots and works well). After that, the “member-verify&#x27;&#x27; channel will be visible.</p><p id="8c6d" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">Step 3: </strong>In the “member-verify” channel, click the <a class="af mu" href="https://verify.staratlas.club/" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">https://verify.staratlas.club/</a> link. It’s pretty straight forward from there. If you get confused there is a nice video in the channel that you can watch.</p><p id="4fe0" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">Step 4:</strong> Once verified, head over to J33VES commands channel. This is where members interact with J33VES.</p><p id="1b3b" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Using the “/” key in the “J33ves-commands” channel of The Club Discord allows you to tell J33ves to do a lot of things. For this article, let’s focus on the commands that are relevant for resupplying your ships.</p><figure class="nd ne nf ng nh lk lc ld paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="ll lm go ln bg lo"><div class="lc ld nc"><picture><source srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*bhahdyv0WUuOOYPw 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bg lp lq c" width="700" height="448" loading="lazy" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="lr ls lt lc ld lu lv be b bf z hb">List of J33ves commands</figcaption></figure><p id="becb" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Start playing around with the commands. <strong class="ly ew">Note: </strong>Commands entered in the commands channel are private. In other words, no one else can see them or the output. The three most important to me were:</p><ul class=""><li id="8e31" class="lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mz mi mj mk na mm mn mo nb mq mr ms mt ni nj nk bj"><strong class="ly ew">/resupply balance</strong>: how much Atlas remains in your J33ves account for resupply purposes.</li><li id="ff24" class="lw lx ev ly b lz nl mb mc md nm mf mg mz nn mj mk na no mn mo nb np mr ms mt ni nj nk bj"><strong class="ly ew">/fleet-supplies</strong>: the amount of resources left before the J33ves bot will kick in. It also gives you the time when J33ves will resupply your ships. Think of this as your early warning system. A way for you to know what’s going on in SCORE without having to connect your wallet to the Galactic Marketplace.</li><li id="52c0" class="lw lx ev ly b lz nl mb mc md nm mf mg mz nn mj mk na no mn mo nb np mr ms mt ni nj nk bj"><strong class="ly ew">/fleet-stats</strong>: shows your fleet, daily rewards, daily burns and net yield.</li></ul><p id="5ac8" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj"><strong class="ly ew">Final verdict and comments</strong></p><p id="ada8" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Overall, this author was impressed with J33ves. I’ve been using the resupply tool for about 5 months now and he has kept my SCORE fleet resourced and happy. Mutinous rumblings have quieted significantly!</p><p id="f27d" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Given how well the tool works, we were somewhat surprised by the small number of active users.</p><figure class="nd ne nf ng nh lk lc ld paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="ll lm go ln bg lo"><div class="lc ld nq"><picture><source srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*D6Y0QPWq08UN4V8l3aMKIg.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bg lp lq c" width="700" height="344" loading="lazy" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="lr ls lt lc ld lu lv be b bf z hb">Active users and total resupplies</figcaption></figure><p id="25db" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">When I asked Loid if the tool was generating any revenue for The Club, he said:</p><blockquote class="mv mw mx"><p id="a1eb" class="lw lx my ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mz mi mj mk na mm mn mo nb mq mr ms mt eo bj">With the price of Atlas where it is, this is not making any notable revenue. You can see in the wallet address what is there and how much it’s worth. We are spending a lot more on it development and upkeep than what it brings in. But that is fine. We are helping the community and building up our reputation and the J33VES name.</p></blockquote><p id="2f9f" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">Putting something to together like this is no easy task. The Club took on the risk (and expense) to create something of real practical utility and opened it up to the entire Star Atlas community. To our knowledge, few Guilds have acted in a similar fashion. So what’s next for J33ves? We heard a rumor that he’s starting to becoming intimately familiar with Chat GPT. Stay tuned for our exclusive article on that soon(tm).</p></div></div></div><div class="ab ca nr ns nt nu" role="separator"><span class="nv bx bl nw nx ny"></span><span class="nv bx bl nw nx ny"></span><span class="nv bx bl nw nx"></span></div><div class="eo ep eq er es"><div class="ab ca"><div class="cb cc cd ce cf cg ch bg"><h1 id="3ec3" class="nz oa ev be ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq or os ot ou ov ow bj">About The Hologram</h1><p id="b6c1" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ox mb mc md oy mf mg mh oz mj mk ml pa mn mo mp pb mr ms mt eo bj">The Hologram is Star Atlas’ first and only independent news network. Our vision is to become the most trusted source of information about Star Atlas and a voice for the whole community. Readers can expect a high standard from our reporting and staff. Our promise to you: we will not publish anything that hasn’t been thoroughly researched and based on the best facts available.</p><p id="33d2" class="pw-post-body-paragraph lw lx ev ly b lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt eo bj">The Hologram is not endorsed or paid by the Star Atlas team. Any information published by The Hologram nor its writers should be considered as informational in nature and does not constitute any financial advice.</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article><div class="ab ca"><div class="ch bg dx dy dz ea"></div></div></div><div clas